Procedure
Installation:
Step-1: Update the system and install java
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install openjdk-8-jdk

Step-2: Become authenticated user
gcloud auth login

Step-3: Download coordinator from bucket
gsutil cp gs://tenfold-prod-db-logs/coordinator-1.0.5-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz /opt

Step-4: Extract coordinator to opt folder
sudo tar -xvz -f /opt/coordinator-1.0.5-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz
Step-5: Add coordinator users
sudo useradd -m coordinator
sudo addgroup coordinator

Step-6: Edit logback.xml file
Go to /opt/coordinator-1.0.5-SNAPSHOT
Change the needed configuration in the logback.xml file.

Step-7: Change owners for coordinator Directories
sudo chown -fR coordinator:coordinator /opt/coordinator-1.0.5-SNAPSHOT

Step-8: Create soft link for coordinator user
sudo ln -sf /opt/coordinator-1.0.5-SNAPSHOT /opt/coordinator
sudo chown -fR coordinator:coordinator /opt/coordinator

Step-9: Create coordinator.service system file
[Unit]
Description=Coordinator
After=network-online.target 

[Service]
ExecStart=/opt/coordinator/coordinator
Restart=on-abort
User=coordinator

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

sudo mv $(pwd)/coordinator.service /etc/systemd/system/

Step-10: Enable coordinator.service system file
sudo systemctl enable coordinator.service

Step-11: Create config.properties file with the following information
Kafka DNS names
Default environment

Cutover Process:
Step 1: Start newer coordinator service in each VM
Start the coordinator service in the newer VMs after setting the proper default environment.

Step 2: Stop older coordinator service in each VM
Stopped the coordinator service in the old vms.
Restart the services
Check the calls in the respective environment.
Check GCP and coordinators logs 

Rollback Process:
Start the Older coordinator services from  vm level
Stopped the new VMs coordinator services.
Restart the pipeline
Check the calls in the respective environment.
Check GCP and coordinators logs

Restart Services after cutover:
We need to restart pipeline on the following deployments:
api
dashboard
processors
schedulers
producers
tracker
tailer
broadsoft, signup-page, realtime-db, gateway
COMMAND:
kubectl rollout restart deploy <All services above mentioned>

Note: Make sure to place IB/OB calls in the environment before and after the cutover


